  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Access to Land and Food Sovereignty Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This grant is a solidarity grant to support BKF&apos;s core work in supporting landless people to access government land which they are entitled to under Bangladeshi law. With CAFOD&apos;s support, BKF will initially scope areas in the country where government land is available and not being distributed to the landless people. BKF will then arrange a serious of workshops to raise awareness on the Land Act, and other legal rights around land. Additionally, BKF will provide awareness to rural communities on food sovereignty. The workshops, will be followed by demonstrations and petitions to the relevant local and national government officials for the right to the land. In incidents where land is not distributed according to the law, BKF will mobilise the landless people to occupy the land, raise their voice and demand their rights. The 3 year support is expected to reach 1,000 landless families in Bangladesh.</narrative>
  </description>
